== NodePresenter

NodePresenter is a very small app that combines the awesome http://shama.github.com/jmpress.js/ project, http://nodejs.org/ and http://socket.io/ to allow remote controll of your jmpress presentations. 


== Getting Started

1. First install the dependencies 
       <tt>npm install .</tt> 

2. Fire up the app 
       <tt>node app.js<tt>

3. Go to http://localhost:3000/ and you'll see a sample presentation:
  

4. Navigate to http://localhost:3000/ on your mobile browser (or desktop browser for that matter) where you need to replace localhost with your machines ip, to see the remote.

5. If your device supports <tt>ondeviceorientation</tt> you can tip it from side to side to trigger slide changes.
